The White House last week issued a factsheet after the 48th G7 summit on the challenges in the 21st century, stressing about those "posed by China". Chinese experts warned that it is just a move by the U.S. to show its own wishful thinking and lure the other six countries in the group to jump onto its anti-China bandwagon. In this episode of BizBeat, CGTN's Michelle Van den Bergh explains why U.S. allies and many countries in the EU do not seem to agree, and in fact oppose isolating China.